public class NewClass {
	static int i = 90;
	static void methodA()
	{
		System.out.println("i in methodA : "+i);
	}
	static void methodB(int x)
	{
		x-=2;
		System.out.println("Integer in methodB : "+x);
	}
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		methodB(i); //global varaiable can be passed as parameter
		System.out.println("i is : " + i);
		
		int a = 62;
		methodB(a);
		System.out.println("a is : " + a);
	}
}

Output:
Integer in methodB : 88
i is : 90
Integer in methodB : 60
a is : 62

So,methods don't change the variables whose values are passed as parameter
